title.narrative: 2.1 INCLUSIVE AND QUALITY EDUCATION

description.narrative: By 2025, the education system has increased capacities to provide inclusive and quality education on relevant skills for work and life, which contributes to Access To Quality Learning Opportunities, Access To Quality Learning Opportunities (Covid), Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2025, adolescents and young people (girls and boys), particularly the most marginalized, are resilient and equipped with skills for life and work and have access to high-quality education in an inclusive and equitable environment.

title.narrative: By 2025, the education system has increased capacities to provide inclusive and quality education on relevant skills for workand life

description.narrative: The education system made progress in the digital transformation of education by releasing a Kosovo-wide e-learning platform, shkollat.org, which contains to date 8,458 learning videos and four instructional video tutorials, and by integrating a core pillar on the digitization of the education system in the draft Kosovo Education Strategic Plan 2022-2026. Digital skills and capacities in facilitation of online learning have been strengthened for 2,000 teachers. UNICEF supported and worked closely with the Ministry of Education, Science, Technology and Innovation to achieve these results. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:18/01/2022
